The process to translate product catalog is complicated because OpenAI translations have bunch
of issues
 1- same term is translated differently at different time. That is problematic for terms that we
 - must have 'consistent' (eg, category names must be same for a given catgory id in different product->category_path records)

 2- Many translations contain text such as "can be translated as ...." - which then have to be manually
  - edited out

Therefore, following is the sequence:
 - We have created a 'stable' (curated) 'termMap' and 'categoryMap'. These contains
 - previously translated english->german translations. The categoryMap contains
 - curated list of catId -> catName map

First run updaterMain to update english catalog to german
    -- python updaterMain

That output needs to be manually editied/verified
    -- manually edited file expected to be in JSON format
        -- output of 'jq' has a missing '[]', ','-at-end-of-each-object, ...
        -- therefore those need to be added in manually to make it a valid json

run manualeditpostprocessor
    -- this uses the curated 'map' files, the english-catalog and manually edited german translation
    -- This script updates the catId->catName, product_type, material values to ensure they are
    -- consistent
        - generates a "processed" .jsonl which can then be indexed
    -- It also generates review.txt
        -- use it to compare results versus english text

